cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.CE, cs.LG 

The paper proposes a time-domain analog-weighted-sum calculation model for neural networks and proposes VLSI circuits to implement the model. This work is related to the field of analog and mixed-signal circuits (cs.ET), as well as artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AR, cs.NE). The proposed model and circuits are designed for energy efficiency (cs.CE) and can be applied to various types of neural network structures (cs.LG).
